<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function parameter 'block' is declared as void * but is only inspected (not modified) when calling mp_ptr_diff_(block, pool->memory). Per MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13, the pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible — here 'block' should be declared 'const void *block'. (Likewise, if pool->memory is not modified elsewhere it should be a const-qualified pointer too.)
